  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  class III-IV by physical status classification system of American Society of
             Anesthesiologist (ASA)

          -  history of arterial vascular disease (arterial hypertension, myocardial ischemia
             and/or cerebral vascular disease)

          -  undergoing elective non-cardiac surgery (hemicolectomy, hernioplasty, laparoscopic
             cholecystectomy and laparoscopic hysterectomy)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  dementia

          -  stroke or myocardial infarction ≤ 6 months before surgery

          -  oncological disease of T2-4N3M1 stage
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
